The author, Nikkie Nguyen, shares her experience as a White House intern in the Office of Presidential Correspondence. She expresses her excitement and motivation to be part of the program and highlights the immense support President Donald J. Trump receives from the American public, which she witnesses by reading the mail he receives. She also mentions how she helps address the hardships faced by Americans and how this experience has given her new perspectives on life, politics, and her future. Nguyen is from Westminster, CA, and is a third-year student studying public administration, criminal justice administration, and communications at California State University, Dominguez Hills.